Changing your tempo, changes what you can get out of pullups. Try these 3 variations from top trainer @andyspeer: plyo, eccentric, and jumping. Plyo pullups build power and increase the gravitational effect on the way down. Eccentric pullups (taking 4 seconds or longer to lower) increase muscle work and help you build up to full range of motion reps. Jumping pullups allow you to cheat to the top position to get more reps while also boosting the cardio and metabolic response.

